                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.516/6–1446</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Thomas W. Lamont</persName>, of New York</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-17">July 17,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lamont</hi>: I acknowledge with appreciation
                    your letter of June 14, 1946 with enclosures, informing this Department of
                    recent correspondence with the Honkgong and Shanghai Banking Corporation
                    regarding steps to be taken towards termination of the China Consortium. The
                    Department would be interested to learn of the action taken with reference to
                    final dissolution of the Consortium, and of the procedure adopted for notifying
                    the Chinese Government.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Clayton</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
